"n. 天赋，本领，才华 【英】 n.天赋，本领，才华( a natural talent or ability; knack) 【记】 和fair(公正的，美丽 的)一起记 【例】 a flair for writing (写作才华) n. 天赋; 才华 = knack = keenness 【记】fl = fly, air: fly到air中去了, 没有天赋行吗? 【记】源自fragrant 芳香的 r=l, g 换了i或被省略(g可不发音，如light)；fly air, 飞天的本事，电影“功夫”中，老丐对小周星驰说:靓仔，你有道灵光从天灵盖喷出，你知不知道？如有一日,你打通任督二脉,还不得飞天啊!→周有天赋，练武奇材 flair (n.)  mid-14c., ""an odor,"" from Old French flair ""odor or scent,"" from flairer ""to smell,"" from Vulgar Latin *flagrare, dissimilated from Latin fragrare ""emit (a sweet) odor"" (see fragrant). Sense of ""special aptitude"" is American English, 1925, perhaps from notion of a hound's ability to track scent."
